For `B`, `B.linked i j` means `B`'s start is `i` and finish is `j`. `B`'s start is `0`, finish is `2`. So `0 = i ∧ 2 = j`.

So we need `i, j` such that `(0 = i ∧ 1 = j) ∧ (0 = i ∧ 2 = j)`. This is equivalent to `0 = i ∧ 1 = j ∧ 0 = i ∧ 2 = j`, which simplifies to `0 = i ∧ 1 = 2`. This is impossible because `1 ≠ 2`.

So `h2` is `False`. This contradicts `h`.

